uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model

Class CNumber

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.CValue<V>
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.CDataValue<INumber>
        • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.CNumber
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CEntity, FEntity

    public class CNumber
extends CDataValue<INumber>
    Represents a numeric-type, defined via a primitive Java Number type and specific numeric range.

      • range

        public static CNumber range(INumber min,
                            INumber max)
        Creates a numeric-type with the specified limits. The number-type will be derived from the specified limit-values, which must have identical number-types, or one of which must represent an infinite value, and hence will not have a specific number-type. If both limits represent infinite values then an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        min - Minimnum value for number-type
        max - Maximnum value for number-type
        Returns:
        Created
        Throws:
        KModelException - if minimnum value is greater than maximnum value, or if minimnum and maximnum values have incompatible number-types

      • range

        min - Minimnum value for number-type
        max - Maximnum value for number-type
        Returns:
        Created
        Throws:
        KModelException - if minimnum value is greater than maximnum value, or if minimnum or maximnum value does not have specified number-type
